{
  "texts": [
    "Among the studies given in Table 4, [43,44] perform a preprocessing step for the input images for their proposed sign language recognition system, which has a 94.7% recognition rate and a 98.07% mAP value, respectively.",
    "In the model we present here, RGB images are studied without any preprocessing on the input images.",
    "This makes the system simple by preventing the process confusion in order to recognize the interested sign.",
    "[45,46] use a Kinect sensor to capture the interested hand sign from the user in their proposed method.As a result of their models, they have presented a sign language recognition system with 99.3% and 96.11% accuracy, respectively.",
    "Although these models give good results, the need for an external reference during the conversation limits the user."
  ]
}